# Session & account identifiers (Keychain)

Source: **`owasp_access_control_policy.md`**, Phase 1 — **`GoDiveKeychainStore`**, **`AppLaunchSessionRestorePresentation`**, **`ReturningAccountHints`**.

## Do

- Store **current profile id**, **returning Apple user id / profile id / display name**, and **cached Firebase UID** via **`GoDiveKeychainStore`** (or the presentation helpers above) — not plain UserDefaults for new work.
- Migrate legacy UserDefaults values into Keychain on read, then remove the legacy key.
- On **sign-out**: clear current profile id + Firebase UID cache (`AccountSession.signOut`).
- On **account delete**: also clear returning-account hints (`ReturningAccountHints.clearAll`).
- Log auth failures with **`Logger`** + **`.private`**; user-facing copy must stay **generic** (`AccountSession.signInFailureUserMessage`).
- Soft-fail Firebase: **never** upsert Firestore without **`Auth.auth().currentUser`** (already required in **`GoDiveFirestoreUserProfileSync`**).

## Do not

- Persist SIWA / Firebase session identifiers only in UserDefaults going forward.
- Log Apple identity tokens, Firebase ID tokens, or UIDs with **`.public`**.
- Use **`print`** for Sign in with Apple failures.
- Invent social write rights from a local SIWA session when Firebase Auth is missing.

## Tests

Use **`GoDiveKeychainStore.testingStore = [:]`** (and `nil` in `defer`) so unit tests do not touch the system Keychain.
